        Conclusions
        The high rate of prescription of parenteral antibiotics
        is a matter of concern. Decreasing the prescribing of
        parenteral antibiotics and an early switch to oral
        <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">antibiotics</ENAMEX> will significantly reduce the expenditure
        incurred. An intravenous to oral antibiotic conversion
